  "name": "Spirit Totem",
  "type": "feat",
  "_id": "LKgkTKi5PdBd04ZM",
  "img": "icons/commodities/treasure/totem-wood-face-brown.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can call forth nature spirits to influence the world around you. As a Bonus Action, you can magically summon an incorporeal spirit to a point you can see within 60 feet of you. The spirit emits a 30-foot Emanation around itself. It counts as neither a creature nor an object, though it has the spectral appearance of the creature it represents.</p><p>As a Bonus Action, you can move the spirit up to 60 feet to a point you can see.</p><p>The spirit persists for 1 minute or until you have the &amp;Reference[incapacitated apply=false] condition. Once you use this feature, you cannot use it again until you finish a Short or Long Rest. Any time before you regain the use of this feature, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape feature to call forth a spirit.</p><p>The effect of the spirit's Emanation depends on the type of spirit you summon from the options below.</p><p><strong>Bear Spirit.</strong> The bear spirit grants you and your allies its might and endurance. Each creature of your choice in the aura when the spirit appears gains Temporary Hit Points equal to 5 plus your Druid level. In addition, you and your allies gain advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws while in the aura.<br /><br /><strong>Hawk Spirit.</strong> The hawk spirit is a consummate hunter, aiding you and your allies with its keen sight. When a creature makes an attack roll against a target in the spirit's aura, you can take a Reaction to grant Advantage to that attack roll. In addition, you and your allies have Advantage on Perception checks while in the aura.<br /><br /><strong>Unicorn Spirit.</strong> The unicorn spirit lends its protection to those nearby. You and your allies gain Advantage on all ability checks made to detect creatures in the spirit's aura. In addition, if you restore Hit Points to any creature inside or outside the aura with a level 1+ spell, each creature of your choice in the aura also regains Hit Points equal to your Druid level.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-DClofSWuArBRXW1k\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>The <strong>Summon Totem</strong> activity will summon a token to represent the totem. This NPC has an <strong>Activate Aura</strong> activity to place the aura around it.</p><p>The <strong>Bear Heal</strong> activity provides a healing roll of the appropriate amount to be applied to the relevant allies. It does not automate the advantage provided by the aura.</p><p>The <strong>Unicorn Heal</strong> activity provides a healing roll of the appropriate amount to be applied to the relevant allies.</p><p></p></section>",
      "chat": ""
    },
